0.text: Answer the following questions. 1. Underline the correct answer. The main character of the poem is pleased by, • seeing the little birds. • seeing the running sheep. • hearing the voices of children. 2. What is the name of the poet? 3. How many stanzas are there in the poem? 4. Write the two lines that say that the children don't like to stop playing. 5. Write rhyming words for the following. • hill - • arise - • play - • sleep - • rest - • sky -
